## Key Design Decisions

### 1. Separation of Concerns

Currently game logic is mixed into `game-server.cjs` (combat, economy, crafting, quests, worlds, player management all in one ~3,100 line file). The new structure __extracts each domain into its own module__ under `systems/`. This makes the game:

- Maintainable (each system independently testable)
- Extensible (new systems drop into the folder)
- On par with modern AAA game engines (Unreal's GameMode/GameState/PlayerController pattern)

### 2. Nexus Integration Layer (`nexus/`)

The `nexus/` directory serves as the bridge between the game engine and the 4,272+ ARC1X backend systems. `arc1x-nexus-bridge.cjs` will:

- Connect to `ARC1X_SYSTEM_INTEGRATION_NEXUS.cjs` (in root)
- Map game events (combat, crafting, world events) to nexus system cycles
